#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md
msgid "Channel Types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md:5
msgid ""
"Channels are used to organize conversations across different topics. "
"There are three types of channels: Public Channels, Private Groups, and "
"Direct Messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md
msgid "Public Channels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md:8
msgid ""
"Public Channels are open to everyone on a team. New team members are "
"automatically a part of two Public Channels: Town Square and Off-Topic."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md
msgid "Private Groups"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md:11
msgid ""
"Private Groups are for sensitive topics and are only visible to select "
"team members. Any member of a Private Group can add additional members. "
"Group members can choose to leave at any time, but only the group owner "
"or Team Admin can remove other members."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md
msgid "Direct Messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md:14
msgid ""
"Direct Messages are for conversations between two team members. These "
"conversations are only visible to the team members involved. The online "
"status indicator next to team members names in the direct message list "
"displays: online (active browser), away (no browser activity for 5 "
"minutes), and offline (browser closed)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md
msgid "Managing Channels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md:17
msgid "Channels can be created, joined, renamed, left and deleted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md
msgid "Creating a Channel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md:20
msgid ""
"Create a new Public Channel or Private Group by selecting the + symbol "
"next to the Channels or Private Groups header on the left hand side. To "
"start a direct message thread, click More at the bottom of the Direct "
"Messages list to view a list of team members you can message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md
msgid "Joining a Channel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md:23
msgid ""
"Click More at the bottom of the Channels list to view a list of Public "
"Channels you can join. To join a Private Group you need to be added by a "
"member of that group."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md
msgid "Renaming a Channel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md:26
msgid ""
"Click the channel name at the top of the center pane to access the drop-"
"down menu, then click Rename Channel. Channel owners can rename the "
"Public Channels or Private Groups they’ve created. Team and System Admins"
" can rename any channel or group."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md
msgid "Leaving a Channel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md:29
msgid ""
"Click the channel name at the top of the center pane to access the drop-"
"down menu, then click Leave Channel. Any team member who leaves a Private"
" Group must be added back by a group member if they wish to rejoin. Team "
"members will not receive mention notifications from channels of which "
"they are not members."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md
msgid "Deleting a Channel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md:32
msgid ""
"Click the channel name at the top of the center pane to access the drop-"
"down menu, then click Delete Channel. Channel owners can delete the "
"Public Channels or Private Groups they’ve created. Team and System Admins"
" can delete any channel or group."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/organizing-conversations.md:34
msgid ""
"When a channel is deleted it is removed from the user interface, but an "
"archived copy exists on the server in case it is needed for audit reasons"
" later. Because of this, the URL of a newly created channel cannot be the"
" same URL name as a deleted channel."
msgstr ""

